# Sequence Diagrams for API Calls

This document contains sequence diagrams for key API calls in the HBnB application. The diagrams illustrate the interaction between the User, API, Business Logic, and Database layers.

---

## 1. User Registration

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant API
    participant BusinessLogic
    participant Database

    User->>API: POST /users (user data)
    API->>BusinessLogic: validate and create user
    BusinessLogic->>Database: INSERT new user
    Database-->>BusinessLogic: user_id
    BusinessLogic-->>API: return user object
    API-->>User: 201 Created (user info)
```

---

## 2. Place Creation

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant API
    participant BusinessLogic
    participant Database

    User->>API: POST /places (place data)
    API->>BusinessLogic: validate and create place
    BusinessLogic->>Database: INSERT new place
    Database-->>BusinessLogic: place_id
    BusinessLogic-->>API: return place object
    API-->>User: 201 Created (place info)
```

---

## 3. Review Submission

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant API
    participant BusinessLogic
    participant Database

    User->>API: POST /reviews (review data)
    API->>BusinessLogic: validate and create review
    BusinessLogic->>Database: INSERT new review
    Database-->>BusinessLogic: review_id
    BusinessLogic-->>API: return review object
    API-->>User: 201 Created (review info)
```

---

## 4. Fetching a List of Places

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant API
    participant BusinessLogic
    participant Database

    User->>API: GET /places?city_id=1
    API->>BusinessLogic: get places by city
    BusinessLogic->>Database: SELECT places WHERE city_id=1
    Database-->>BusinessLogic: list of places
    BusinessLogic-->>API: return places list
    API-->>User: 200 OK (places data)
```
